tourBios.exmtStatus: Top 8, 2000 SENIOR PGA TOUR National Qualifying Tournament
tourBios.carHigh: 1999: Highlight of his year came in his second start of the season at the Bell Atlantic Classic of the season. Was one stroke off the lead after 36 holes at Hartefeld National and closed with a one-under-par 71 for seventh, his previous best performance ever on the SENIOR TOUR...Among the top 15 two weeks later at the Cadillac NFL Golf Classic. Shot 67 on Saturday at Upper Montclair and eventually finished T13...Returned to the SENIOR TOUR National Qualifying Tournament in the fall and earned a conditional exemption for the 2000 season. Was involved in a five-way playoff after posting a 72-hole score of 2-over 290. Bogey on the second extra hole dropped him into the 13th spot.1998: Finished 12th at the 1998 SENIOR TOUR National Qualifying Tournament to earn a conditional exemption for 1999...Played in six tournaments during the campaign, open-qualifying for five of them...Finished T8 in his first SENIOR TOUR start at the Saint Luke's Classic and won $27,500...Also had a T8 at the AT&T Canada Senior Open in Calgary.
tourBios.otherCarHigh: Played in a number of mini-tour events around the country while prepping for the SENIOR TOUR and accumulated 47 victories in various tournaments...Made three starts on the PGA TOUR in his career...Played in the 1994 and 1997 GTE Byron Nelson Classic and the 1997 LaCantera Texas Open, but did not make the cut in any of them...Played in the 1997 NIKE Monterrey Open...Attended PGA TOUR National Qualifying Tournament three times (1994, 1995, 1997)...Has had three holes-in-one.
tourBios.personal: Had his own home remodeling business for nearly 20 years...Began playing at age 25, after he drove by a driving range and got hooked on the game...In his spare time, he enjoys cookouts with his family...Among his heroes are Jack Nicklaus, Arnold Palmer and fellow Dallas resident Lee Trevino...One of his biggest thrills in golf is making a long putt in front of a large gallery.

dyn.dynResults: His best finish on the PGA TOUR Champions was T2nd in 2001 at the Novell Utah Showdown.
